Fix up handling of final backslash (#4)

Previous method would fail on input that really is valid: a final escape
sequence consisting of two literal backslashes.

Better escape encoding/decoding

With this change now it is possible to read and write backslashes at the end of
field, because backslashes are interpreted one by one.

See: https://github.com/solidsnack/tsv/issues/4

Check number of fields by default

In case if provided data source contains invalid data, throw error immediately,
by default, with optional possibility to skip errors issuing a warning.

See: https://github.com/solidsnack/tsv/issues/3
